cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of Artificial Intelligence methods to playing card games, including Jass.
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the challenge of games with hidden information and the use of AI agents to play such games.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as many AI methods for playing card games involve machine learning techniques.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) may be relevant as the paper discusses the difficulty of developing AI agents that can outperform top human players in Jass.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) may be relevant as the paper may discuss the implementation of AI agents for playing card games.
